item.title: Demography and deathcare in a changing East Asia
item.description: As East Asian countries like Japan, China and South Korea experience rapid population ageing due to declining fertility rates and increasing life expectancy, the demographic shift in the land of the living is having a parallel impact on what happens after life. Deathcare -- which encompasses post-death services, products, policy, and governance -- is changing too... Feed: https://media.rss.com/ear-to-asia/feed.xml
